gomodel:SYNGO_2678  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: LRRC4C KO mice showed impaired post-tetanic depression (PTD) in hippocampus MPP-DG pathway.\n\n21/2/2018 Pim\nFig.7: \"Disappearance of presynaptic netrin-Gs in NGL-KO mice\"\n\nFig.8: \"Synaptic localization and surface expression levels of netrin-Gs regulated by postsynaptic NGLs. \"\n- \"... total amounts of P2-netrin-G1 were decreased in NGL1-KO mice (Fig. 8A). The reduction of SPM-netrin-G1 was more evident in NGL1-KO mice (Fig. 8B). Consistent with the biochemical data, immunohistochemical analysis revealed a markedly reduced intensity for netrin-G1 in NGL1-KO mice (Fig. 8C).\"\n- LRRC4C is located at the postsynaptic membrane (Fig.1, see also ticket #2221)\n- Interacts with presynaptic netrin-G1 (Fig.1, see also ticket #2321)\n- PMID:14595443 shows the adhesive properties of LRRC4C and netrin-G1.\n- Conclusion is that pre/postsynaptic netrin-G1/LRRC4C modulate synaptic transmission via cell-cell-adhesion.. Experimental description: Materials and Methods\nElectrophysiology.\nMice were deeply anesthetized with halothane (Takeda) and killed by decapitation." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6194-9648" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5518-6584" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2678" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

